w the riverfront’s ruined buildings assumed a powerful erotic role and gave the area a distinct identity. By telling the story of the piers as gentrification swept New York and before the AIDS crisis, Anderson unearths the buried histories of violence, regeneration, and LGBTQ activism that developed in and around the cruising scene.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCruising (Sexual behavior)zNew York (State)zNew York. 0aRuins in art. 0aSexual minority communityzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aWaterfronts in art. 0aWaterfrontsxSocial aspectszNew York (State)zNew York. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aDavid Wojnarowicz.  aNew York City history.  acruising.  agentrification.  aqueer.  aurban renewal.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2019z9783110605747oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226603896423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226603896/original  a978-3-11-061001-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DADb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019